content.markdown:
Inserting Memory Cards

# Using Two Cards

The camera can be used with two cards, one in each of its two
slots. At default settings, photos are saved to the card in the sec-
ond slot only when the card in the first slot is full. This can be
changed using SAVE DATA SET-UP > CARD SLOT SETTING.

| Option | Description | Display |
| --- | --- | --- |
| SEQUENTIAL (default) | The card in the second slot is used only when the card in the firstslotisfull. Ifthe second slotis selectedfor 8 SAVE DATA SET-UP > SELECT SLOT( SEQUENTIAL), recording will start on the card in the second slot and switch to the first slot when the card in the second slot is full. | 1 |
| BACKUP | Each picture is recorded twice, once to each card. | 1 2 |
| SEPARATE | RAW pictures are recorded to the card in the first slot and JPEG or HEIF pictures to the card in the sec- ond slot. This setting takes effect only when SUPER FINE+RAW, FINE+RAW, or NORMAL+RAW is se- lected for I.Q. IMAGE QUALITY SETTING > IMAGE QUALITY. | 1 2 V RAW+JPEG 1 2 R : RAW+HEIF |


The card used to store movies can be selected using 원 MOVIE
SETTING > MEDIA REC SETTING.
